{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"193cffb9cde36024","type":"text","text":"[11/06 09:27] Jin DongHwan\nyou mentioned... \nThere is a timing issue with the too small to pick code. The background process needs to be improved to take this into account\n\n[11/06 10:09] Laver, Jonathan\nYes the function YOUNG_NAM_CheckTooSmallToPick is run in the background and only checks to see if all dus are too small to pick. SORT_LANE_LOC_SetTmLocation checks to see if the last carton that is not too small to pick has reached the sort lane. But if this carton never arrives then we have a problem. We need to expand YOUNG_NAM_CheckTooSmallToPick to check that there are no more cartons left that are not too small to pick\n","x":-538,"y":-434,"width":727,"height":327},
		{"id":"49209386c88bb22e","type":"text","text":"```\nGLOBAL BOOLEAN PICK_ShouldAbandonByTooSmallToPick( \n    REC_NO PickRecNo )\n{\n  REC_NO DespatchGroupRecNo = NULL_REC_NO;\n  REC_NO SkuUomRecNo;\n  \n  POS_INT DespatchGroupFillLevel;\n  POS_INT PiecesPerEach = 1;\n  POS_INT FillLevel = 0; \n\n  if( !PICK_ValidRecNo( PickRecNo ) )\n    return FALSE;\n  \n  REC_NO ProdRecNo = PICK_GetProdRecNo( PickRecNo );\n\n  REC_NO DuRecNo = PICK_GetDuRecNo( PickRecNo );\n\n  if( !DU_ValidRecNo( DuRecNo ) )\n    return FALSE;\n\n  DespatchGroupRecNo = DU_GetDespatchGroupRecNo( DuRecNo );\n\n  if( !DESPATCH_GROUP_ValidRecNo( DespatchGroupRecNo ) )\n    return FALSE;\n\n  if( PROD_ValidRecNo( ProdRecNo ))\n    SkuUomRecNo = SKU_GetSkuUomRecNo( PROD_GetSkuRecNo( ProdRecNo ), SKU_UNIT_EACH, SKU_DIMS_BASE );\n\n  if( SKU_UOM_ValidRecNo( SkuUomRecNo ))\n    PiecesPerEach = SKU_UOM_GetPiecesPerEach( SkuUomRecNo );\n\n  FillLevel = PICK_GetQty( PickRecNo )*PiecesPerEach;\n\n  if( !PICK_GetApplyFillCriteria( PickRecNo ) )\n    return FALSE;\n\n  if( PICK_GetRepickCount( PickRecNo ) >= 1 )\n    return FALSE;\n\n  DespatchGroupFillLevel = DESPATCH_GROUP_GetFillLevel( DespatchGroupRecNo );\n\n  // If Despatch Fill is greater than the DU Fill; the DU doesn't meet the criteria.\n  if( DespatchGroupFillLevel > FillLevel )\n    return TRUE;\n  else \n    return FALSE;\n\n} /* end PICK_ShouldAbandonByTooSmallToPick */\n```","x":-549,"y":51,"width":623,"height":168},
		{"id":"23f4f3ade7f58528","type":"text","text":"```\nGLOBAL void YOUNG_NAM_CheckTooSmallToPick()\n{\n  REC_NO DuRecNo;\n  REC_NO OrderRecNo;\n  REC_NO PickRecNo;\n  DYN_LIST_TYPE *DuList;\n  POS_INT DuTooSmallToPickCount;\n\n  DuList = DYN_LIST_New( sizeof(REC_NO), 10, NULL_POS_INT );\n  \n  LOOP_ALL_ORDERS\n  {\n    if( ORDER_GetOrderState( OrderRecNo ) < OP_STATE_RESERVED )\n      continue;\n\n    if( GL_InList( ORDER_GetOrderState( OrderRecNo ),\n                   OP_PICKED_STATES ) )\n      continue;\n\n    DuTooSmallToPickCount = 0;\n    DYN_LIST_Reset( DuList );\n\n    ORDER_GetDuList( OrderRecNo, DuList );\n\n    LOOP_ALL_DYN_LIST_RECNOS( DuList, DuRecNo )\n    {\n      if( DU_IsHeldBy( DuRecNo, OP_HOLD_EnumToRecNo( OP_HOLD_BY_TOO_SMALL_TO_PICK ) ) )\n        DuTooSmallToPickCount ++;\n    }\n\n    LOOP_ALL_DYN_LIST_RECNOS( DuList, DuRecNo )\n    {\n      if( DYN_LIST_GetCount( DuList ) == DuTooSmallToPickCount )\n      {\n        if( DU_CanSetAbandoned( DuRecNo ) )\n        {\n          HOST_SendDuStatus( DuRecNo, OP_STATE_ABANDONED );\n\n          if ( !DU_SetAbandoned( DuRecNo, \"TOO SMALL TO PICK\", \"TOO SMALL TO PICK\", TRUE ) )\n          {\n            LOG_Event( EVENTS, \"%s: Failed to abandon DU %s: %s\",\n                __FUNCTION__, DU_GetDuId( DuRecNo ), DU_ErrorString );\n          }\n        }\n        else\n        {\n          LOG_Event( EVENTS, \"%s: Cannot abandon DU %s: %s\",\n              __FUNCTION__, DU_GetDuId( DuRecNo ), DU_ErrorString );\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    POS_INT RemainingDuToPickCount = DYN_LIST_GetCount( DuList ) - DuTooSmallToPickCount;\n    if (RemainingDuToPickCount > 0)\n    {\n      LOOP_ALL_DYN_LIST_RECNOS(DuList, DuRecNo)\n      {\n        if (!DU_IsHeldBy(DuRecNo, OP_HOLD_EnumToRecNo(OP_HOLD_BY_TOO_SMALL_TO_PICK)))\n        {\n          LOOP_ALL_DU_PICKS\n          {\n            if( PICK_ShouldAbandonByTooSmallToPick( PickRecNo ))\n              PICK_SetAbandoned( PickRecNo, \"Too Small To Pick\", \"Too Small To Pick\", TRUE );\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  DYN_LIST_Free(DuList);\n```","x":122,"y":53,"width":400,"height":203},
		{"id":"45669ca1fbe2c4fe","type":"text","text":"YOUNG_NAM_CheckTooSmallToPick should check to see if all DUs that are not too small to pick are greater than PICKED","x":-521,"y":461,"width":490,"height":126},
		{"id":"299b93a39e0f3277","type":"text","text":"If there is nothing left to pick then abandon the too small to pick","x":-60,"y":677,"width":541,"height":65},
		{"id":"30b65605d95c1a63","type":"text","text":"```\nGLOBAL void YOUNG_NAM_CheckTooSmallToPick()\n{\n  REC_NO DuRecNo;\n  REC_NO OrderRecNo;\n  REC_NO PickRecNo;\n  DYN_LIST_TYPE *DuList;\n  POS_INT DuTooSmallToPickCount = 0;\n  POS_INT DuLeftToPickCount = 0;\n\n  DuList = DYN_LIST_New( sizeof(REC_NO), 10, NULL_POS_INT );\n  \n  LOOP_ALL_ORDERS\n  {\n    if( ORDER_GetOrderState( OrderRecNo ) < OP_STATE_RESERVED )\n      continue;\n\n    if( GL_InList( ORDER_GetOrderState( OrderRecNo ),\n                   OP_PICKED_STATES ) )\n      continue;\n\n    DuTooSmallToPickCount = 0;\n    DuLeftToPickCount = 0;\n    DYN_LIST_Reset( DuList );\n\n    ORDER_GetDuList( OrderRecNo, DuList );\n\n    LOOP_ALL_DYN_LIST_RECNOS( DuList, DuRecNo )\n    {\n      if( DU_IsHeldBy( DuRecNo, OP_HOLD_EnumToRecNo( OP_HOLD_BY_TOO_SMALL_TO_PICK ) ) )\n        DuTooSmallToPickCount ++;\n      else if( DU_GetDuState( DuRecNo ) < OP_STATE_PICKED )\n        DuLeftToPickCount++\n    }\n\n    LOOP_ALL_DYN_LIST_RECNOS( DuList, DuRecNo )\n    {\n      if( DuLeftToPickCount == 0 )\n      {\n        if( !DU_IsHeldBy(DuRecNo, OP_HOLD_EnumToRecNo(OP_HOLD_BY_TOO_SMALL_TO_PICK) ) )\n          continue;\n        \n        if( DU_CanSetAbandoned( DuRecNo ) )\n        {\n          HOST_SendDuStatus( DuRecNo, OP_STATE_ABANDONED );\n\n          if ( !DU_SetAbandoned( DuRecNo, \"TOO SMALL TO PICK\", \"TOO SMALL TO PICK\", TRUE ) )\n          {\n            LOG_Event( EVENTS, \"%s: Failed to abandon DU %s: %s\",\n                __FUNCTION__, DU_GetDuId( DuRecNo ), DU_ErrorString );\n          }\n        }\n        else\n        {\n          LOG_Event( EVENTS, \"%s: Cannot abandon DU %s: %s\",\n              __FUNCTION__, DU_GetDuId( DuRecNo ), DU_ErrorString );\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  DYN_LIST_Free(DuList);\n}\n```","x":-503,"y":646,"width":404,"height":231},
